Distribution and ecology. P. m o u r i t z i sp. nov. is known from only three small shallow salinas in the Hyden-Lake King area of the Wheatbelt (
Fig. 4
). Given this restricted distribution and the secondary salinisation of two of them, Timms et al. ( 2009 ) recommend it be given Priority One status under the Western Australian Department of Conservation’s priority species listing process.
